MEMC Receives Boost in Line of Credit to $550 Million

-- B y   W i l l   W a d e
-- 
2011-03-25T13:10:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/memc-receives-boost-in-bank-of-america-line-to-550-million.html
(Corrects size of earlier credit facility in second
paragraph of story published March 24.)  MEMC Electronic Materials Inc. (WFR) , a
U.S. supplier of polysilicon for solar cells and semiconductors,
increased its line of credit with  Bank of America Corp. (BAC)  to $550
million.  The amended revolving credit facility was disclosed in a
regulatory filing today. It replaces a $250 million credit
facility.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Wade at 
 wwade4@bloomberg.net  